\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 A GUI based lua script to link FX parameters across different tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This plugin runs a backgound task that links the selected tracks, ensuring that the plugin configurations of the 2 FX chains match\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i A full Guide can be found {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/mattia-marini/ReaperLink/blob/main/Guide.pdf"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
here
}}}
}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Usage:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Run {\i "Marini_FX linker background tasks"} or configure automatic startup (see below)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Toggle Ui with {\i "Marini_FX linker toggle UI.lua"} to create/remove links\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Features:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Linking {\b every} parameters of {\b every} plugin across different tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Linking state is saved on project basis\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab GUI based link managment\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Multiple tabs support and hot project reloading\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flexible and roboust linking\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Zero dependency script}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Automatic startup:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In order for the script to work, a background task should be running i.e., to make synching happen, you have to run the "Marini_FX linker background tasks" script every time you open Reaper. To make that happen automatically you can run the "Marini_FX linker toggle autostart". (you can see a script state next to its description in action list. Once set to on, the script will automatically launch on next startup)\par}
}
